**Airbnb, Inc.** operates an online marketplace for lodging, primarily homestays for vacation rentals, and tourism activities. Since its founding in 2008, the company has expanded its offerings to include Experiences, which allow locals to offer activities to travelers. As of my last update in 2023, Airbnb boasts millions of listings in more than 220 countries and regions, illustrating its vast global market presence and its ability to disrupt traditional hotel and accommodation sectors.
